      <akn:section eId="sec_44_1633">
        <akn:num>44-1633</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Appropriation for expenditure or accumulation of endowment fund; rules of construction.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_44-1633_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_44-1633_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>To limit the authority to appropriate for expenditure or accumulate under subsection (a) of this section, a gift instrument shall specifically state the limitation.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_44-1633_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Terms in a gift instrument designating a gift as an endowment, or a direction or authorization in the gift instrument to use only “income”, “interest”, “dividends”, or “rents, issues, or profits”, or “to preserve the principal intact”, or words of similar import:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
